&gt;&gt; I mean, I've been watching
you, and it's very impressive.

00:17:38.390 --> 00:17:39.723
[ Inaudible Remark ]

00:17:40.390 --> 00:17:42.323
&gt;&gt; Does someone want to talk?

00:17:45.240 --> 00:17:47.773
Oh, okay. They're walking
the mic over.

00:17:51.580 --> 00:17:53.180
[ Inaudible Discussion ]

00:17:53.980 --> 00:17:56.313
&gt;&gt; They told me to walk to the mic.

00:17:57.520 --> 00:17:58.520
&gt;&gt; Well, okay.

00:17:59.520 --> 00:18:00.920
Walk [inaudible] mic.

00:18:01.520 --> 00:18:02.786
&gt;&gt; Oh, that's good.

00:18:03.520 --> 00:18:07.920
&gt;&gt; In Evensong, you have a beautiful
paragraph there about longings

00:18:08.370 --> 00:18:12.636
and desire and the origins of it,
and I was fascinated with that.

00:18:15.530 --> 00:18:18.996
That's the reason why I
picked up Unfinished Desires.

00:18:19.950 --> 00:18:24.483
Are you expanding that particular
concept of longings that are hidden

00:18:28.440 --> 00:18:31.440
and can be explained
eventually in one's life?

00:18:32.890 --> 00:18:33.280
&gt;&gt; May I take you with me
on the rest of my trip?

00:18:35.700 --> 00:18:36.700
&gt;&gt; Sure.

00:18:38.470 --> 00:18:39.603
&gt;&gt; Actually, yes.

00:18:40.470 --> 00:18:41.840
Did everyone hear her
question, longings and desire?

00:18:42.500 --> 00:18:43.510
Are you working on it-- are
you still working on it?

00:18:44.890 --> 00:18:45.890
Yes, I am.

00:18:46.890 --> 00:18:50.756
And my new novel is-- I made
even more of a pressure cooker

00:18:51.690 --> 00:18:54.890
with just a few people
with longings and desires.

00:18:56.490 --> 00:18:59.090
Yes, I want to get
really down in there.

00:18:59.210 --> 00:19:00.210
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:19:01.210 --> 00:19:02.210
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:19:03.210 --> 00:19:04.210
&gt;&gt; Okay.

00:19:05.210 --> 00:19:06.210
&gt;&gt; Yes?

00:19:07.210 --> 00:19:08.276
&gt;&gt; Hi. I want-- would
like to know who are some

00:19:09.210 --> 00:19:11.676
of your favorite contemporary
writers,

00:19:11.750 --> 00:19:13.683
and what are you reading now.

00:19:14.750 --> 00:19:15.750


00:19:16.680 --> 00:19:19.880
&gt;&gt; I had just finished--
I just hate to say this.

00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:23.586
You're not gonna believe it.

00:19:23.890 --> 00:19:27.156
But I just reread Anna
Karenina and War and Peace,

00:19:30.070 --> 00:19:34.136
and I'm rereading Hilary Mantel's,
Wolf Hall, with great envy.

00:19:40.070 --> 00:19:43.803
I read every book-- every
literary novel that comes out--

00:19:48.410 --> 00:19:49.820
when it comes out, because that's
when I do in the evenings now.

00:19:51.200 --> 00:19:53.600
I read as I watch a couple of shows,

00:19:54.530 --> 00:19:58.396
like the Rachel Maddow [phonetic]
show or [inaudible] show,

00:20:01.390 --> 00:20:04.056
and Masterpiece Mystery
and Doctor House,

00:20:08.270 --> 00:20:10.470
and Boardwalk Empire and Mad Men.

00:20:11.770 --> 00:20:12.836
That's about it.

00:20:13.770 --> 00:20:14.770
[ Laughter ]

00:20:15.770 --> 00:20:16.770
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:20:17.770 --> 00:20:19.370
&gt;&gt; I think I have read every
literary novel that's come

00:20:19.770 --> 00:20:20.770
out this year.

00:20:21.770 --> 00:20:25.236
And I've read, of course,
Jonathan Franzen's Freedom.

00:20:29.280 --> 00:20:32.413
I was looking at my old
interview that they take

00:20:33.370 --> 00:20:36.970
for the first Book Festival,
and someone was asking me,

00:20:39.490 --> 00:20:41.423
"What have you been reading?"

00:20:41.490 --> 00:20:45.623
and I said I'm reading this new
author called Jonathan Franzen,

00:20:46.040 --> 00:20:49.306
Corrections, and I'm
rereading Jane Austen's Emma.

00:20:50.040 --> 00:20:51.573
So it's about the same.

00:20:52.190 --> 00:20:56.456
And I reread Elizabeth Bowen a
lot, and my new novel, I will say,

00:20:58.660 --> 00:21:00.593
is my tribute to Henry James.

00:21:00.980 --> 00:21:04.913
I have been fascinated by the
Turn of the Screw for decades.

00:21:04.930 --> 00:21:09.130
And now, I'm gonna write my Turn
of the Screw with a bow to him.

00:21:09.970 --> 00:21:10.970
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:21:11.970 --> 00:21:13.170
&gt;&gt; You're welcome.

00:21:13.970 --> 00:21:14.970
&gt;&gt; Hi, Gail.

00:21:15.970 --> 00:21:16.970
&gt;&gt; Hi.

00:21:17.970 --> 00:21:19.703
&gt;&gt; Hi. I attended the school,
as you know, that you wrote

00:21:19.970 --> 00:21:21.836
about in Unfinished Desires.

00:21:21.970 --> 00:21:23.436
&gt;&gt; What year were you?

00:21:23.970 --> 00:21:25.836
Or do you want-- never mind.

00:21:25.970 --> 00:21:27.303
&gt;&gt; No, I don't mind.

00:21:27.970 --> 00:21:28.970
[ Laughter ]

00:21:29.970 --> 00:21:33.636
&gt;&gt; '56. And now, I just--
I've write it twice, actually,

00:21:34.530 --> 00:21:36.330
and I just really loved it.

00:21:37.120 --> 00:21:40.720
And I was wondering if you
had any response from people

00:21:41.790 --> 00:21:44.656
who might recognize
themselves in the novel.

00:21:46.170 --> 00:21:47.370
&gt;&gt; Well, not-- no.

00:21:48.400 --> 00:21:50.266
But long before I wrote it--

00:21:51.630 --> 00:21:51.753
in fact, when I was
writing another book--

00:21:54.240 --> 00:21:54.640
when I was writing
a Southern Family,

00:21:56.240 --> 00:21:56.623
I wanted to get some information on
that order, that religious order.

00:22:00.390 --> 00:22:00.463
And by mistake, my
researcher put me in touch

00:22:03.250 --> 00:22:07.583
with the original Mother Ravenel
who did not get her claws into me

00:22:09.180 --> 00:22:12.580
because I left town before
I got to her [inaudible].

00:22:13.150 --> 00:22:17.350
But then, she reconnected with
me in her old age and my old age,

00:22:19.160 --> 00:22:22.826
and she started sending me
tapes telling me how to write

00:22:24.100 --> 00:22:25.900
and what words to leave in.

00:22:26.100 --> 00:22:27.100
[ Laughter ]

00:22:28.100 --> 00:22:29.433
&gt;&gt; I can see it now.

00:22:30.100 --> 00:22:30.233
&gt;&gt; So I got an insight into her.

00:22:32.100 --> 00:22:32.370
It was very valuable, that you know,

00:22:34.230 --> 00:22:36.830
we wanna keep control
over what we have.

00:22:36.980 --> 00:22:40.446
She wanted to keep control
over one of her old girls.

00:22:40.510 --> 00:22:45.110
So she very much influenced me in
terms of looking and seeing how much

00:22:47.850 --> 00:22:48.360
of me was in her, and how she could
get have a spiritual right life

00:22:51.740 --> 00:22:52.740
as well.

00:22:53.740 --> 00:22:55.006
&gt;&gt; Good. Thank you.

